#11: Name and IP address of the device that makes the link between you (local network) and the outside world
#The NAT server (network address translation) modifies the source IP address of packets; Wikipedia
#states that NAT has become virtually synonymous with IP masquerading. One Internet-routable
#IP address of a NAT gateway can be used for an entire private network, conserving address space.
#In other words, NAT allows multiple private devices with their own private IP addresses to access
#the Internet through a common public/global address.
#On the school network, calling traceroute gives as the second hop "nat.hive.fi" with IP address of 10.60.1.1.
